< Review>
TRULY ABOVE & BEYOND! I called Inspection Pro purely by accident, due entirely to a rookie mistake made by an inexperienced customer service agent at PG&E- a mistake I am so glad they made!
Having just rented our house less than a week prior, I was ofcourse trying to get all the utilities turned on & in my name. I was scheduled for a Saturday, "all-day" appt, meaning PG&E can show up to turn your power on Saturday anytime between 8am-8pm. So after sitting & waiting all day & still no power, I decided to call & find out why; & after sitting through another 45 minutes of prompts & hold music, I was finally speaking to a very new, very inexperienced, although very helpful young human. When he finally managed to pull up my acct, he was able to tell me that PG&E didnt miss my appt, they had been there at 2 o'clock that afternoon & determined that my panel needed an inspection before they could restore services to my address, not that they walked 15feet to my front door to tell me that or called even to let me know there was no need to waste the remainder of a beautiful Saturday afternoon waiting for power, cuz it wasnt comin anytime soon! Nah... So there i was, looking forward to another long weekend with 5 kids & still no water or the power that they were promised would be on by that Sat night, with no idea what to do next, on the phone with the nicest customer service agent ever who was unfortunately just as clueless as me at that point, so on the verge of helpless tears I asked him what i should do next. He asked me to hold while he searched somethin real quick & when he came back on the line he gave me the number to INSPECTION PRO & told me "They can help". Even though it was now late Sat night, i figured i could call & leave a message so maybe id be first to get a call back Monday. To my surprise, Allen answered! He patiently listened to my whole story, tears & all & when i was done he made an appt to come out and take a look the next day! on a SUNDAY, with zero notice!!  And he showed up just like he said he would & then called me with his very thorough report that evening, he then explained that his services would usually cost this much etc etc, but since he knew what a rough time I was having, knowing theres no way i could even afford his very reasonable fees, he made me an offer that wouldnt break my bank and was more than fair, if anything I kinda feel like i took advantage of him & his very thorough services!
Overall, he was very Professional, yet Down to Earth & Understanding at the same time. I would recommend Allen & Inspection Pro 100%!< /Review>

<Review>BEWARE OF THIS TRANSMISSION SHOP.
I TOOK A 2012 NISSAN TO THIS LOCATION FOR HAVING SOME TROUBLE WITH THE TRANSMISSION, AFTER DIAGNOSTIC ,THE OWNER TOLD ME THAT THE TRANSMISSION NEEDS TO BE REPLACED AND IT WILL COST $3600 INCLUDE PARTS AND LABOR, I TOOK THE CAR TO ANOTHER PLACE TO GET A QUOTE AND THE PROBLEM WASNT TRANSMISSION AT ALL IT WAS A PROBLEM WITH A SENSOR THAT DETECTS THE SPEED AND SEND SIGNAL TO THE TRANSMISSION AND I GOT IT FIXED FOR $100 .IT'S BEEN 2 MONTH SINCE I GOT IT FIXED AND NO PROBLEMS.
DO NOT TRUST THE ESTIMATE OF THIS PLACE AND GET A SECOND OPINION FIRST BEFORE YOU GET RIPPED OFF BY THIS THIEVES.< /Review><Pictures>None< /Pictures><resp>{'time': 1410554141578, 'text': "Mrs. Li Zhang,\nYou are not telling the whole story. Your car had been in an accident and you bought it at an auction with a salvage title. You expressed to us that you did not know anything about this vehicle. So we helped you as much as we could answering all your questions and doing a full diagnosis without charging you a penny. Many years of technical training and the use of a very expensive Lab scope allowed us to see that the speed signal  coming out of the transmission speed sensor was erratic. We removed the speed sensor and found out that something inside the transmission has been hitting it causing some scratches in it. Next we used a boroscope to find out what was causing the damage and found out that a part inside the transmission was loose and intermittently it was getting in between the sensor and the signal triggering component. Even though the sensor was scratched it was still working because it was not broken. We were able to push the loose piece out of the way so the sensor would read. Once we did that the transmission worked fine, as a matter of fact it drove fine when you picked it up, didn't it? So replacing the sensor was not the proper repair. you asked us what would be the worst case scenario to fix the problem and we told you that replacing the transmission with a new unit from the dealer would be the worst case and the cost would be close to $ 3,600.00.  We never told you that that was going to be the cost to fix your car. We needed to disassemble the transmission and fix what was broken only. I understand you had the sensor replaced somewhere else and the car has been driving fine for a couple of months now, but we know it is  unlikely to last too long. It is just a matter of time for the loose piece inside the transmission to cause the same damage the old sensor had to the new sensor. I wonder why it was so easy for you to call us thieves since all we did was to help you without charging you anything and when we told you there was not obligation from you to get the repairs done at our shop.\nSincerely.\nFabian"}<//resp><gmapID>0x80d959cd1b11ba6f:0x398aa08482ad142d<//gmapID></record>

<Review>Love my newly straightened teeth! Like many people I know who had braces as kids, I was guilty of not wearing my retainer after treatment and ended up with crooked teeth again.

This second time around, I was not about to mess around and knew I was going to take straightening them seriously. I called and scheduled a consultation with ease, visited Dr. Tajaddod's practice, got a quote for Invisalign, and began treatment pretty quickly. Not gonna lie, it was fairly expensive, but ultimately it was worth it. There are certainly less expensive "order online" options, but IMO, it's better to work with a seasoned orthodontist.

Treatment was estimated to take 1 year, but ended up taking 1.5 years. Each visit after the 1 year mark, I initially felt frustrated that it was taking longer than expected, but like I originally told myself, I wasn't messing around this time, and neither was Dr. Tajaddod. She continued to work with me until my teeth were perfect. Despite treatment taking 50% longer than expected, she kept ordering more trays for me until my teeth were just right and she never charged any additional $.

I just had my 6 month follow up after treatment ended, and you can bet I've definitely been wearing my retainers every day! I'm scheduled for a follow up in one year to make sure everything is still in order - a meeting I don't think I had when I got braces the first time. I appreciate Dr. Tajaddod's thoroughness and that she really cares that her patients get the best results possible. Thank you to Dr. Tajaddod and her staff. Love my new smile! :)< /Review>< pics>

< Text>
Really good orthodontist. Dr. Merna Tajaddod is incredibly talented, and her staff is good too. There's this one-star review here on the review section and I think that's more the style she works in. She's very busy and I get the feeling her mind is firing all the time. She knows what to do and has her schedule for you laid out to be the most optimal for you, which does not require a lot of time for one sitting sometimes. I'd argue that she's efficient with her time. To clarify this a bit more; I'm 27 years of age and my teeth are quite crooked. They classified me as a hard case and put me on invisalign. Even though the appointments were mostly check-ins like the 1-star review mentioned, overall I've been put on a great personal schedule that works for my teeth. It's an art to create the right braces/retainers to gradually shape your teeth, and she's done an incredible job for me.

The remark that I do have is that Dr. Tajaddod does not share what she is thinking. I did not really have an idea of the invisalign structure and timeline that applied to me, and which events would happen at what times. So make sure you ask and be forward about this.

Overall stellar service and they make sure you'll look amazing.</Text>

<time>1510628311930< /time>< Review>
When I went to see Dr. Tajaddod for my free consultation, I learned that I was a surgical case and my treatment involved jaw surgery. At first, I was afraid of the surgery which made me hesitant about starting treatment. After the consultation with Dr. Tajaddod, I felt confident in her hands and trusted her with my treatment. She was very direct and professional when she explained the treatment plan.

Her office has a warm and caring vibe. The staff there is very friendly and won't hesitate to address your concerns. Don't be afraid to ask questions or express any discomfort because they will take care of you. During my treatment, I actually looked forward to my appointments!

My treatment lasted about two and a half years and I'm extremely pleased with the results. I highly recommend getting a consultation if you're thinking about getting braces.</Review>

< rate>
5</rate>
< text>
This is a relatively easy trail to access one of the most spectacular views in the Southland. I say relatively because it is by no means easy, just a lot easier than the ski hut trail. Devil's Backbone itself is a little hairy, so if you're afraid of heights, don't even try it. Make sure you bring mire water than you can imagine needing and be prepared for colder than expected weather and lots of wind. Well worth the effort.< /text>

<text>Hiked the trails alone Oct. 29, 2017. The trails strenuous,  hard, very steeps. I love the Devil's Back Bone Trail. The scenery were just amazingly breathing. This was my first time hiking Mt. Baldy "San Antonio". I had a great experienced and I had fun alone hiking the trails.

Beginner, Moderate and Hard hikers are welcome to hike. Make sure to bring foods and waters.

<Review>I've placed about 10 orders with this Budee and have always been more than satisfied with the selection, special offers/bundles, and speedy customer service via text.  I even can recall helping on of their UX team members troubleshoot a page layout issue that I had noticed in my browser.  Budee was cool -- something has changed, however.

After growing tired of waiting 3+ hours for an unscheduled delivery , I thought I would give scheduling a delivery a try.  I've tried it twice and had to reschedule my orders both times because the delivery wasn't going to happen within the delivery time frame I had confirmed.  It's not the end of the world, I just now know to think of the delivery window as broader than what I am quoted (for example, despite confirming a 5-6pm delivery window, my order arrived at 7:20pm tonight).

The drivers are also friendly and efficient.  I've never had a problem using Vault and I let them know that they have a tip to collect, too.  TONIGHT's ambassador, however.... my god.  She was waving her phone screen and yelling from the car that she didn't have to get out and that I need to be better about my delivery instructions. My ankle is sprained and I kindly asked her to come to the door.  She yelled back (still parked in the middle of a quiet residential street) that she didn't' have to and that I should've told her that on the phone.  Again, I asked "so what do you want to do?"  She replied that she was coming but only "this time" and then she dropped the bag on the porch step, instead of placing it within arm's reach (I was wearing a mask to protect us both).  Because I had to step down from the door threshold (with my crutches) my dog sneaked past me and approached her.  He's harmless, but I can 100% imagine why his approaching her would make her uncomfortable.  The encounter was fine but also avoidable if her behavior didn't require my walking away from the front door.  Anyway, she quickly left my property and I couldn't make out all of the cursing and back talk that she wanted me to hear.

Just SOOOO unnecessarily nasty.

I wish Budee could deliver like they used to... I'll give it another try, but I won't get my hopes up.< /Review>< Pics>

<Time>1596393077436<//Time><Name>Jack Tomberlin< /Name><Resp>{'time': 1572063408573, 'text': 'Hi John, its always our pleasure to serve you!!'}<//Resp>< Review>
A Love Letter:
Living in Rancho Cucamonga, there are few locally-owned, let alone woman-owned, places for a great meal. Not only does it have a great beer and cocktail selection, 4th & Mill explores the boundaries of what a sports bar can be. Whether it's Sunday brunch, Jamaican food, or taco Tuesday, their food is anything but your standard sports bar fare. Having gone on these menu experiments with them for years, I can attest, it is always a hit. Lastly, none of it matters without a great staff. The first beer I ordered after moving was from their bartender Carly. She's remembered my name ever sense. The owners often work the floor themselves and have done a fantastic job hiring well and encouraging great attitudes.<//Review>

<rate>5<//rate>< text>
A Love Letter:
Living in Rancho Cucamonga, there are few locally-owned, let alone woman-owned, places for a great meal. Not only does it have a great beer and cocktail selection, 4th & Mill explores the boundaries of what a sports bar can be. Whether it's Sunday brunch, Jamaican food, or taco Tuesday, their food is anything but your standard sports bar fare. Having gone on these menu experiments with them for years, I can attest, it is always a hit. Lastly, none of it matters without a great staff. The first beer I ordered after moving was from their bartender Carly. She's remembered my name ever sense. The owners often work the floor themselves and have done a fantastic job hiring well and encouraging great attitudes.<//text>

< review>
We arrived here at 12:30 a.m. on a Monday night/Tuesday morning. There was a small, fun crowd. The kitchen was still open, which was great. There's a full restaurant menu, not just bar food. They kept serving food until close. (Extra star for that. It's hard to find late night food in the IE!) The service was good, and the food was pretty tasty. We had a chicken Caesar salad ($16 with chicken), and the grilled chicken had a nice flavor. The shrimp tacos were big ($6 each) and also loaded. You can get the shrimp grilled or fried. Bottomless chips and salsa were $5. I had two old fashioneds. She had a couple fruity drinks. (The pirate punch was pretty good.) We got out of there for less than $100 with food and four cocktails, including tip.) The music is hip hop, not loud enough to drown out conversation. There are two pool tables and a mix of booths and tables for seating.</review>
